Auth model:
  - All routes go through requireWorkspaceJwt (mounted at /v1/workspaces/*).
  - Each handler ALSO cross-checks that the JWT's workspace_id matches the
    path :workspaceId (`guardWorkspace`); mismatch → 403 forbidden, malformed
    path UUID → 400 invalid_workspace_id. Defense in depth so a leaked JWT
    can't address other workspaces even if the middleware ever changes.

Storage model:
  - storage_state_json column stores a POINTER to a Browserbase Context,
    never raw cookies / localStorage. Browserbase itself owns the secret
    state — POST connect creates a fresh Context, attaches a session
    pinned to it with persistContext:true, surfaces the live view URL.
    POST finalize stops the session (which causes Browserbase to persist
    cookies+localStorage into the Context) and rewrites the pointer to
    its final shape.
  - Pointer shapes:
      pending   = { kind: 'browserbase_context_pending', contextId, sessionId, initialUrl }
      finalized = { kind: 'browserbase_context', contextId }
  - GET list NEVER returns storage_state_json (nor a camelCase mirror).
    Tested explicitly in browser-sites.test.ts.

